main event: A bright white light with a meteor-like appearance was observed in Bryan, Ohio in January 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for more than 10 minutes.,The light changed from bright white to gradually dimmer yellow.,The object appeared to have erratic velocity.,The sighting was concluded to likely be a meteor based on its characteristics.,There were no unusual phenomena noted by the University of Wisconsin Observatory on the night of the sighting.
sighted object: one bright light in the sky
